entries.femaleVariant: Hey.
I'm just checking the suspension. The hydraulics have to be shipshape – we're in for a bumpy ride.
Given our plan any thought?
And you? Rested?
Can I help?
No, you can't. I'll be done soon. The Raffens left her crooked as a bag of snakes.
Get in, V.
V. Get. In. The. Car. You've got to be freezing.
Great. Hop in, it's cold out here.
Did you sleep all right?
Are you ready to go?
Can't complain.
And you? Reasonably rested?
I think you had nightmares. You screamed a few times.
Born that way.
'Member, need Hellman alive, unharmed. Gotta try not to blow the AV to bits, OK?
I know. But I'd say your man had best be buckled in. This idea... if it works, he'll be in for a rough landing.
Satwave power station?
Why's the AV gotta come down there?
Why down the AV there, at that exact spot?
Because once it's on the ground, we'll have to locate it and grab your target. As fast as we can.
Um, satwave power station?
And the terrain there is typical California desert – flat, dry and empty. They'll be a big old sitting duck.
And then we strike. We hit the AV with an EMP.
As soon as the AV is in range, we cause an electromagnetic pulse. The on-board electronics should fail outright.
'Course we do.
Meaning what? Engines'll shut down?
Everything will shut down, engines included. Drive, navigation, communication systems…
[Step away] Well, let's get to work.
AV'll fly over the power station, we're sure of that?
Hello.
Really?
Don't worry, I'm accustomed to that sort of thing. When Mitch and Scorpion came back from the war, they tossed and turned night after night. For months this went on.
All right. Let's ride.
Aren't you, um, counting chickens? We can't actually know the AV'll fly over the station.
Yes. We need to break into it.
Mhm, so far so good. But then what?
So we're taking the EMP route?
Power station? Wait, you wanna use an EMP?
Bullseye.
But... how? We can't generate that sort of pulse on command.
Would you like to bet me?
We drive up to the power collection unit, break in and override the controls, lift any limiters.
As soon as the AV is in range, we set off the electromagnetic turbopulse. This should smoke the AV's systems.
So the drive, navsystems...
...communications. Everything, out like a light. They won't stand a chance in hell!
And you? Sleep well?
Like a baby on a bumpy road.
That ol' HMG of yours?
My gun will be useful elsewhere. This caliber would barely dent the armor of a heavy hitter like that.
There are other ways. Here – the clamp's our solution. A satwave power station.
It's bound to be quite a ride, but not one you'll regret. I've got everything planned out.
Of course, we can't. But we don't have to. You'll see.
Hey, Panam.
We're the wrench. The cutter is the AV. And the screwdriver is where the AV should bury its nose cone in the dust.
Now, you must be wondering how we get the AV to do that.
Look here.
Are you interested in hearing this?
V? I thought we needed to do this quickly.
Need a hand?
Come up with anything? For Hellman, I mean.
As a matter of fact, I did.
Whatever it is, it'll pass.
Uh-huh... let's hope so.
[Lean in] OK, hit me with it.
OK, tell me.
Explain it to me again.
Hold up, one more time. Wrench is our car, right?
Mhm. The cutter is the AV. The screwdriver is where the AV should hit the ground.
And the clamp is the satwave power station. That is, the net we use to bring the AV down.
V? Hello?
Well, do you have any thoughts?
'Member, need Hellman in one piece.
It's all settled then, right? You'll be back here at dark.
[Wait for Panam]
[Get in]
